transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling back, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hi, how are you?

Speaker 1: I'm good, how are you?

Speaker 2: Not bad, a little ticked off at you guys.

Speaker 1: I tried stopping this and canceling my subscription a month ago,

Speaker 2: and apparently that didn't go through.

Speaker 1: I was just billed again.

Speaker 2: So you need to tell me how I cancel this.

Speaker 1: Okay, Mark Pickman in El Paso, Texas?

Speaker 2: That's correct.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: Did you try to email us the cancellation?

Speaker 1: No, I went to the website, which they told me that's how I can cancel it.

Speaker 2: There's no place to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so that's exactly why it didn't get canceled,

Speaker 2: whether you would have had to have called in.

Speaker 1: We do all cancellations over the phone verbally.

Speaker 2: So you're in El Paso, Texas.

Speaker 1: Well, how come it didn't get canceled the last time I called then?

Speaker 2: Did you accidentally call the number that was on the pill bottle?

Speaker 1: That's to our pharmacy.

Speaker 2: All they're going to do is delay the next shipment, not cancel.

Speaker 1: I didn't have another number.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's who I did call.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Either way, I'll make sure everything going forward is canceled.

Speaker 1: You do have this last one already sent out to you.

Speaker 2: I can't stop that.

Speaker 1: So if you don't want it, Mark, don't tear it up.

Speaker 2: When it arrives, the packaging, don't do anything to it.

Speaker 1: Just shake it up.

Speaker 2: Make sure there's pill bottles in there.

Speaker 1: After that, write return to sender on it with a marker or a pen.

Speaker 2: Put it back in the mailbox.

Speaker 1: Mailman will take it tomorrow.

Speaker 2: When is it arriving?

Speaker 1: Next time he comes by.

Speaker 2: And then we'll issue the refund as soon as we get it back.

Speaker 1: Sounds good.

Speaker 2: So I'm canceled officially now.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: I already did that myself right now.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Take care.
